<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[818,1444,449,733]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[818,878,450,468]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Notes:</emphasis>
We here propose the new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Camacho and Feitosa" authorityYear="2022" box="[1199,1278,449,469]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Boltonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1278,449,469]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Boltonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate a single species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Borgmeier 1957)" authorityName="Camacho &amp; Franco &amp; Branstetter &amp; Pie &amp; Longino &amp; Schultz &amp; Feitosa" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Camacho &amp; Franco &amp; Branstetter &amp; Pie &amp; Longino &amp; Schultz &amp; Feitosa" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[973,1248,479,499]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Boltonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microps">
<emphasis box="[973,1074,480,498]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. microps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier, T." box="[1090,1240,479,499]" journalOrPublisher="An. Acad. Bras. Cienc." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="103 - 128" part="29" refId="ref17469" refString="Borgmeier, T. 1957. Myrmecologische Studien. An. Acad. Bras. Cienc. 29: 103 - 128." title="Myrmecologische Studien" type="journal article" year="1957">Borgmeier 1957</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, formerly a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1887" box="[845,972,509,527]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Heteroponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,972,509,527]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Heteroponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species represents a divergent lineage at the base of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolton" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Camacho &amp; Franco &amp; Branstetter &amp; Pie &amp; Longino &amp; Schultz &amp; Feitosa" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[892,1033,537,557]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Heteroponerini">Heteroponerini</taxonomicName>
and is the sister-group of all the remaining species in the tribe. The genus name is an homage to Barry Bolton, legendary ant taxonomist and author of Bolton’s Catalogue of Ants of the World, which is the very foundation of all taxonomic papers published in myrmecology since 1994.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
